            <note type="compositionNote">According to Fut I. 347, this work was written in 595H,
                  in 11 days during the month of Ramadan. It is dedicated to al-Habashi.</note>
            <!-- Contents -->
            <noteGrp type="workDesc">
               <note type="description">Written for IA’s close companion, Badr al-Ḥabashī, this
                     is said to be the book that explains what all spiritual masters need to teach.
                     It describes three degrees of surrender (islām), faith (īmān) and true goodness
                     (iḥsān), according to three levels of realisation. It includes a detailed
                     discussion of how all the members and faculties of the human being participate
                     in the Divine Praise.</note>
               <note type="structure"/>
               <note type="contentsNote"/>
            </noteGrp>
            <!-- Stemmatics -->
            <note type="stemmatics">A much copied work, verified by at least four historic mss.
                  The best is Yusuf Ağa 5001, written by SQ in the lifetime of IA, with a samāʿ
                  signed by IA, although it is badly water-damaged, and Majles 594 (652H) which is
                  taken from a copy made in Damascus in 606H. Other mss identified by JC: Bayazid
                  3466 (735H?)</note>
